All the news

   All the news

   Research integrity, French Office for Research Integrity (OFIS)

Gustave Roussy reaffirms its commitment to research integrity

   Publications, Science and Technology Observatory (OST)

Europe produces more scientific publications than China and the USA, but the
USA still leads in terms of excellence

   "Dynamics of Scientific Production in the World, in Europe and in
   France, 2000-2016", published today by Hcéres, studies scientific
   output in the world, in Europe and in France. The report devotes
   special attention to the impact of the growth in Chinese output on
   bibliometric indicators for other countries. The report thus provides a
   complement to recent analyses of the positioning of research-intensive
   countries.

   French Office for Research Integrity (OFIS), Research integrity

Inrap signs the French Charter for Research Integrity

